    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>For big, formal weddings or small, informal ones, the bride's dress is white, even when the groom wears flip-flops. Pageantry and spectacle were in bloom last month at the Conservatory Garden, on Fifth Avenue at 104th Street. The most charming bridal bouquets were those that appeared to have been picked fresh from the garden and tied with a ribbon, rather than tortured into a shape. The veil under a chignon (bottom, second from far right) was an elegant statement.</p>
      </block>
